
1. Botswana is Africa’s oldest continuous democracy, going on since 1966
2. One of the Seven Natural Wonders of Africa, Okavango Delta, is located in Botswana.
3. Botswana has Africa’s highest concentration of elephants - over 130,000!
4. Over 70% of Botswana’s total area is actually a desert
5. Botswana contains one of the world’s largest salt pans
6. The Okavango Delta in Botswana has over 500 species of birds, making it
a birdwatcher's paradise. Even for non-birdwatchers, the beautiful inland
river delta is a sight to behold.
7.